## `<file-level: overview>`
<!-- checksum: rust-blobs-1 -->

### Purpose
Chunked file content storage. All public functions take `chunk_size: u64` explicitly (pinned per-filesystem at mkfs time, loaded from `schema_version`). An empty file has ZERO rows in `blobs` — not a placeholder row.

Chunk math:
- Chunk for byte offset `O` is `chunk_id = O / chunk_size`.
- In-chunk offset is `O % chunk_size`.
- A write of `N` bytes starting at `O` touches chunks `O/S ..= (O+N-1)/S`.
- Every chunk except possibly the last is exactly `chunk_size` bytes; absent chunks read as zeros (POSIX hole semantics).

### Implementation Notes

```rust
use rusqlite::{Connection, params};
use std::collections::HashMap;

use crate::errors::Result;
```

---

## `pub fn read_range(conn, inode, offset, size, file_size, chunk_size) -> Result<Vec<u8>>`
<!-- checksum: rust-blobs-2 -->

### Purpose
Read up to `size` bytes starting at `offset`. Short-reads past EOF. Returns empty vec if `offset >= file_size`.

### Preconditions
- `chunk_size > 0`.

### Postconditions
- If `offset >= file_size` or `size == 0`: returns empty vec.
- Else: returns `content[offset .. min(offset+size, file_size)]` where `content` is the concatenation of every chunk's `data`, with absent chunks read as zeros.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn read_range(
    conn: &Connection, inode: u64, offset: u64, size: u64,
    file_size: u64, chunk_size: u64,
) -> Result<Vec<u8>> {
    if offset >= file_size || size == 0 {
        return Ok(Vec::new());
    }
    let end = (offset + size).min(file_size);
    let actual = (end - offset) as usize;
    let first = offset / chunk_size;
    let last  = (end - 1) / chunk_size;

    let mut stmt = conn.prepare(
        "SELECT chunk_id, data FROM blobs
         WHERE inode = ?1 AND chunk_id BETWEEN ?2 AND ?3
         ORDER BY chunk_id",
    )?;
    let mut present: HashMap<u64, Vec<u8>> = HashMap::new();
    let rows = stmt.query_map(
        params![inode as i64, first as i64, last as i64],
        |r| Ok((r.get::<_, i64>(0)? as u64, r.get::<_, Vec<u8>>(1)?)),
    )?;
    for row in rows { let (cid, data) = row?; present.insert(cid, data); }

    let mut out = Vec::with_capacity(actual);
    for cid in first..=last {
        let chunk_start = cid * chunk_size;
        let lo = offset.saturating_sub(chunk_start).min(chunk_size) as usize;
        let hi = (end - chunk_start).min(chunk_size) as usize;
        let want = hi - lo;
        match present.get(&cid) {
            Some(data) => {
                let slice_lo = lo.min(data.len());
                let slice_hi = hi.min(data.len());
                out.extend_from_slice(&data[slice_lo..slice_hi]);
                let pad = want - (slice_hi - slice_lo);
                if pad > 0 { out.extend(std::iter::repeat(0u8).take(pad)); }
            }
            None => out.extend(std::iter::repeat(0u8).take(want)),
        }
    }
    debug_assert_eq!(out.len(), actual, "chunk math bug");
    Ok(out)
}
```

