## `pub fn count_chunks(conn, inode) -> Result<u64>`
<!-- checksum: rust-blobs-5 -->

### Purpose
Test-introspection hook. Returns the number of chunk rows for the inode.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn count_chunks(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<u64> {
    let n: i64 = conn.query_row(
        "SELECT COUNT(*) FROM blobs WHERE inode = ?1",
        params![inode as i64],
        |r| r.get(0),
    )?;
    Ok(n as u64)
}
```

---

## `pub fn total_bytes(conn, inode) -> Result<u64>`
<!-- checksum: rust-blobs-6 -->

### Purpose
Test-introspection hook. Sum of `length(data)` across chunks. Diverges from `stat.size` when holes exist.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
pub fn total_bytes(conn: &Connection, inode: u64) -> Result<u64> {
    let n: i64 = conn.query_row(
        "SELECT COALESCE(SUM(length(data)), 0) FROM blobs WHERE inode = ?1",
        params![inode as i64],
        |r| r.get(0),
    )?;
    Ok(n as u64)
}
```

